(4102,577,"location_description","Known as the “Paso del Norte”, Ciudad Juarez serves as a key link between Mexico and the United States and is an important high technology manufacturing area with world-class human resources.\r\n\r\nBi-national commerce and trade at the Ciudad Juarez border crossing is a constant way of life and historic tradition. The city shares cultural, economic and social ties with El Paso, its sister city in Texas.\r\n\r\nIn addition to its historic designation as “El Paso del Norte”, Ciudad Juarez represents a clear example of the link between Mexico and Texas, sharing cultural, economic and social ties with El Paso, its sister city in Texas.\r\n\r\nCiudad Juarez is the largest urban center on the U.S./Mexico border. Its principal activity is the maquiladora manufacturing industry and it has at least 18 industrial parks and ample availability of qualified labor in communications, transportation and services infrastructure.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Through its office in Ciudad Juarez, CCN handles foreign investment, real estate, litigation and corporate matters for our clients’ operations in the State of Chihuahua.</li>\r\n</ul>"),
