(4367,602,"location_description","Cacheaux, Cavazos &amp; Newton has maintained an office in McAllen, Texas since the firm’s inception in 1994. Founding partner Daniel Cavazos leads the firm’s McAllen office, located in the heart of the dynamic South Texas-Northern Mexico manufacturing region.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe firm’s McAllen office features both Mexico and U.S. licensed attorneys, who focus on corporate, real estate, manufacturing, business, estate planning, labor, environmental, health and safety issues. The firm works closely with local economic development organizations, including the McAllen Economic Development Corporation and the Brownsville Economic Development Council (BEDC) to assist clients in Mexico and South Texas.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe firm’s McAllen, Reynosa and Matamoros offices are strategically located in the cities with the most industrial and commercial growth in the region and allow CCN to support clients on both sides of the Texas-Mexico border."),
