(4443,612,"location_description","San Antonio is South Texas’ leading center of trade, financial and professional services, and, since 1994, has been the site of CCN’s home office and is led by the firm’s founding and managing partner, Joseph B. Newton.\r\n\r\nWith a population of approximately 2.5 million residents, the San Antonio metropolitan area is one of the fastest growing regions in the United States . San Antonio is widely considered as the city with the most Mexican roots in the United States.  It is also a focal point for United States investors conducting projects in Mexico, as well as a site for Mexican businesses and investors entering the Texas and U.S. markets.\r\n\r\nCCN’s <strong>San </strong>Antonio<strong> lawyers</strong> represent and advise clients in a wide variety of industries on U.S., Mexican and cross-border legal matters. Both Mexican and U.S.-licensed attorneys work in the firm’s downtown office and travel frequently throughout Mexico."),
