(14395,2079,"location_description","Mexico City, also known as the Distrito Federal, occupies the heart of Mexican life and culture and is one of the largest, most dynamic, cosmopolitan and important cities in the world. Mexico City sits at the confluence of the country’s ideas and future plans, serving as the capital seat of federal power.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSince its founding in 1994, CCN has maintained an office in Mexico City, which provides a full range of legal services to its clients. Such work includes commercial and international law, including real estate, litigation, labor and tax. CCN’s Mexico City office facilitates the firm’s efforts to liaise with federal authorities on issues related to foreign investment, antitrust, economic development and immigration, among many others."),
