(15666,2157,"location_description","Guadalajara, also known as the Silicon Valley of Mexico, is Mexico’s second largest city and is strategically located close to Mexico City and the Bajío area. The Guadalajara metropolitan area is widely considered to be an attractive destination for foreign investment in Mexico. Guadalajara is also a leader in technological innovation and design, as well being an agribusiness hub. This dynamic city hosts some of the top universities in the country.\r\n\r\nCCN’s Guadalajara office is fully equipped to serve clients in Guadalajara, Mexico’s West Coast (Occidente) and the Bajío area, providing a wide range of legal services to its clients. Such work includes corporate, commercial and international law, including real estate, customs, trade and tax matters."),
