(31379,5035,"location_description","As a neighbor of San Diego, California, and only 135 miles from the seaports of Los Angeles and Long Beach, Tijuana is a major port of entry to Latin America. Tijuana is one of the most dynamic cities in the world, with more than 300,000 border crossings per day between San Diego, California and Tijuana, Baja California. The city is now part of the bi-national megalopolis known as “Cali Baja”, which comprises San Diego and Imperial Counties in California, as well as the state of Baja California, with a combined population of more than 6.5 million people. Tijuana’s strategic geographical location, infrastructure and highly qualified workforce have enabled it to consistently attract investments from large manufacturing corporations, especially in the electronics, medical device and aerospace sectors.\r\n\r\nCCN opened its seventh Mexican office in Tijuana in order to enable the firm to serve clients from North America, Europe and Asia who are located in Tijuana, Mexicali, Ensenada, Tecate, La Paz and the Los Cabos area, as well as in the state of Sonora. CCN´s Tijuana office advises clients on labor, real estate, foreign investment and corporate matters, among others."),
